article.headline: Sacramento State 76, Portland State 60
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Alex Bausley had 21 points, six rebounds and five assists to lead Sacramento State over Portland State 76-60 in the Big Sky Conference opener Thursday night. Loren Leath and Haron Hargrave had 15 points each for the Hornets (10-5, 1-0 Big Sky), who haven't won a conference opener since the 1999-2000 season. Sacramento State scored the win despite losing leading scorer Jason Harris, who's expected to miss four conference games after being declared academically ineligible. The Hornets missed 11 of their first 12 shots before hitting five 3-pointers to gain a 25-18 lead. Despite 16 turnovers and giving up eight steals to Sacramento State, Portland State (7-7, 0-1) only trailed at the half 28-21. In the second half, the Hornets were more focused offensively as they pushed their lead to 60-40 on Clark Woods' layup at the 7:32 mark. With poor shooting and terrible ball-handling, the Vikings finished the game with 24 turnovers. Juma Kamara had 17 points and Josh Neely added 10 for the Vikings, who ended a five-game winning streak.
